1
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:34,094
We need to put him on ECMO.

2
00:01:35,161 --> 00:01:35,562
Director.

3
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:40,133
Severe heart failure, recurrent ventricular fibrillation.

4
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:41,434
We have to start

5
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:41,868
ECMO now.

6
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:42,936
You're his legal guardian.

7
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:43,436
Do you consent?

8
00:01:45,004 --> 00:01:45,605
Sign here.

9
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:49,943
Lin Yi.

10
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:57,117
Sign? Where?

11
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:07,927
For ECMO.

12
00:02:10,530 --> 00:02:11,064
Come with me.

13
00:02:17,370 --> 00:02:18,505
How did it suddenly get this bad?

14
00:02:19,105 --> 00:02:19,772
I don't know.

15
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:21,908
I... I got home,

16
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:23,009
and he was already like this.

17
00:02:24,444 --> 00:02:24,944
This afternoon,

18
00:02:25,011 --> 00:02:26,246
he looked fine on the monitor.

19
00:02:26,479 --> 00:02:27,413
He took his medicine

20
00:02:27,714 --> 00:02:28,314
every day too.

21
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:29,115
Lin Yi.

22
00:02:30,016 --> 00:02:30,683
Listen to me.

23
00:02:31,151 --> 00:02:32,752
Xiaorui's condition is very serious.

24
00:02:33,953 --> 00:02:35,255
Even with ECMO,

25
00:02:35,922 --> 00:02:37,357
we don't know how long it can sustain him.

26
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:39,125
Use a donor heart.

27
00:02:39,359 --> 00:02:40,593
We've been on the waiting list for a long time.

28
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:41,828
We can use a donor heart.

29
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:43,730
There isn't enough time.

30
00:02:45,331 --> 00:02:46,599
His right heart function is very poor.

31
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:47,734
An LVAD won't work either.

32
00:02:49,969 --> 00:02:51,271
No. You have to save him.

33
00:02:52,105 --> 00:02:52,805
You have to save him.

34
00:02:53,773 --> 00:02:54,307
Please save him.

35
00:02:54,307 --> 00:02:55,308
I'm begging you.

36
00:02:56,142 --> 00:02:56,643
Please.

37
00:02:57,043 --> 00:02:57,710
You have to save him.

38
00:02:58,678 --> 00:02:59,212
He...

39
00:02:59,946 --> 00:03:01,014
He can't end like this.

40
00:03:01,281 --> 00:03:02,282
He can't.

41
00:03:03,016 --> 00:03:03,683
I'm begging you.

42
00:03:03,783 --> 00:03:04,884
Think of something.

43
00:03:04,884 --> 00:03:05,552
Please save him.

44
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,721
The only possible option now

45
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:11,958
is biventricular assist support.

46
00:03:13,393 --> 00:03:14,494
But Dongjiang can't do it.

47
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:15,562
Okay.

48
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:16,829
Biventricular support. Fine.

49
00:03:17,397 --> 00:03:18,198
Implant the device.

50
00:03:18,598 --> 00:03:19,399
I have money.

51
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:20,600
How much? How much does it cost?

52
00:03:20,733 --> 00:03:22,802
I... I've saved a lot.

53
00:03:22,835 --> 00:03:23,670
Any amount is fine.

54
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:24,671
We'll do biventricular support.

55
00:03:24,671 --> 00:03:26,005
Please help me.

56
00:03:26,406 --> 00:03:27,040
Please help me.

57
00:03:27,407 --> 00:03:27,907
Help me.

58
00:03:28,308 --> 00:03:29,008
Please.

59
00:03:32,145 --> 00:03:32,946
I'll try.

60
00:04:16,823 --> 00:04:17,323
Director Zhou.

61
00:04:17,890 --> 00:04:19,225
Biventricular artificial heart support

62
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:20,226
has not yet been formally

63
00:04:20,226 --> 00:04:21,294
approved for routine clinical use.

64
00:04:21,628 --> 00:04:22,362
But several major hospitals

65
00:04:22,362 --> 00:04:23,763
in China

66
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:25,198
are authorized for clinical trials.

67
00:04:25,565 --> 00:04:26,666
I've contacted a few.

68
00:04:26,799 --> 00:04:28,234
A hospital in Shanghai

69
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:29,369
is willing to accept him.

70
00:04:29,736 --> 00:04:30,436
I don't know

71
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:31,237
how Xiaorui is doing now.

72
00:04:31,371 --> 00:04:32,271
Can he be transported?

73
00:04:32,772 --> 00:04:33,439
He's on

74
00:04:33,439 --> 00:04:33,906
ECMO for now.

75
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:34,974
If he stabilizes,

76
00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:35,908
we can find a way to transfer him.

77
00:04:36,209 --> 00:04:36,909
I'm coming over now.

78
00:04:39,012 --> 00:04:39,612
It's too far.

79
00:04:39,879 --> 00:04:41,047
An ambulance won't work.

80
00:04:41,147 --> 00:04:42,148
We need a helicopter.

81
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:43,383
Does Dongli Hospital

82
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:44,283
have any agreement

83
00:04:44,283 --> 00:04:45,051
with general aviation services?

84
00:04:45,652 --> 00:04:46,719
The emergency medical center

85
00:04:46,753 --> 00:04:47,687
may be able to coordinate it.

86
00:04:47,887 --> 00:04:48,388
Okay.

87
00:04:48,755 --> 00:04:49,689
I'll contact them.

88
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:50,823
I'll also ask

89
00:04:51,024 --> 00:04:51,557
private rescue organizations.

90
00:04:51,691 --> 00:04:52,525
Let's split up.

91
00:04:52,759 --> 00:04:53,159
All right.

92
00:04:56,329 --> 00:04:57,163
The blood gas results are back.

93
00:04:58,865 --> 00:05:00,033
The lactate is even higher.

94
00:05:01,768 --> 00:05:02,669
It's over 25.

95
00:05:06,372 --> 00:05:07,573
His blood pressure is falling too.

96
00:05:31,664 --> 00:05:32,365
A hospital in Shanghai

97
00:05:32,398 --> 00:05:33,800
will accept Xiaorui for biventricular support.

98
00:05:34,434 --> 00:05:35,668
We're contacting a helicopter.

99
00:05:40,907 --> 00:05:41,441
Prepare for transfer.

100
00:05:42,108 --> 00:05:42,642
We found one.

101
00:05:43,276 --> 00:05:43,910
Director Xiaofeng

102
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,011
arranged biventricular support.

103
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:45,878
We're going to Shanghai now.

104
00:05:45,878 --> 00:05:46,646
The helicopter is already...

105
00:06:27,053 --> 00:06:28,921
Can... can it still fly?

106
00:06:37,263 --> 00:06:37,930
Yes.

107
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:42,535
Transfer him.

108
00:06:43,503 --> 00:06:43,970
Transfer him.

109
00:06:44,203 --> 00:06:44,670
Um...

110
00:06:44,871 --> 00:06:45,304
Dr. Qiao.

111
00:06:45,605 --> 00:06:46,439
Take the ECMO team

112
00:06:46,439 --> 00:06:46,973
and equipment with you on the flight.

113
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:47,507
Beibei.

114
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:49,709
You come help too.

115
00:06:49,709 --> 00:06:50,243
I'm transferring him.

116
00:06:50,276 --> 00:06:50,943
Everyone, help.

117
00:06:50,943 --> 00:06:51,544
I'm transferring him.

118
00:06:51,611 --> 00:06:52,111
Director Lin.

119
00:06:53,513 --> 00:06:54,347
Is there still any point

120
00:06:55,448 --> 00:06:56,382
in flying now?

121
00:06:56,516 --> 00:06:57,383
Of course there is.

122
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:00,953
He can't die.

123
00:07:06,793 --> 00:07:07,927
Can we please not give up?

124
00:07:11,631 --> 00:07:12,565
I'm begging you.

125
00:07:14,367 --> 00:07:15,134
Please.

126
00:07:17,036 --> 00:07:17,603
Help me.

127
00:07:24,143 --> 00:07:24,911
Then we'll fly.

128
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:29,615
I'll go with you.

129
00:07:39,826 --> 00:07:40,426
Director Zhou.

130
00:07:41,227 --> 00:07:41,828
But...

131
00:07:42,328 --> 00:07:42,862
Brother.

132
00:07:51,471 --> 00:07:52,505
He hasn't given up.

133
00:07:56,042 --> 00:07:57,343
We can't leave him with regret.

134
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:09,455
President.

135
00:08:09,755 --> 00:08:10,389
President Wang.

136
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:13,292
Director Lin

137
00:08:13,526 --> 00:08:14,794
still wants the transfer,

138
00:08:15,161 --> 00:08:15,828
to Shanghai.

139
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:22,969
Give me the penlight.

140
00:08:39,852 --> 00:08:40,953
Both pupils are fully dilated.

141
00:08:41,988 --> 00:08:43,122
No light reflex.

142
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:44,757
He is likely brain-dead.

143
00:08:47,927 --> 00:08:48,728
The transfer stretcher is here.

144
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:50,863
The stretcher is here.

145
00:08:58,070 --> 00:08:58,604
Xiao Lin.

146
00:09:01,674 --> 00:09:02,275
The patient

147
00:09:03,676 --> 00:09:04,477
is already brain-dead.

148
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:07,446
If we go through all this

149
00:09:07,446 --> 00:09:09,215
to transfer him now,

150
00:09:10,983 --> 00:09:11,984
there's no point.

151
00:09:29,268 --> 00:09:30,570
As his family,

152
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:32,471
I understand

153
00:09:36,175 --> 00:09:37,009
how you feel.

154
00:09:39,445 --> 00:09:40,446
But as a doctor,

155
00:09:42,315 --> 00:09:43,049
you need to be rational.

156
00:09:43,282 --> 00:09:44,050
Don't touch me.

157
00:09:48,387 --> 00:09:49,322
I'm not a doctor right now.

158
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:51,123
And you're not my superior.

159
00:09:52,124 --> 00:09:52,625
I'm family.

160
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:53,359
I'm his family.

161
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,527
I demand a transfer.

162
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:55,561
I demand

163
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:56,195
that the hospital transfer him immediately.

164
00:09:56,195 --> 00:09:57,363
Will you cooperate or not?

165
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:02,969
Forget it. I'll do it myself.

166
00:10:03,336 --> 00:10:04,070
Lin Yi.

167
00:10:04,804 --> 00:10:05,605
Lin Yi.

168
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:06,973
If you won't help, I will.

169
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:08,708
Lin Yi.

170
00:10:09,075 --> 00:10:10,443
This is also the choice you should make.

171
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:18,718
A matching donor is rare.

172
00:10:19,285 --> 00:10:20,786
It should be reserved for your own family,

173
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:22,922
so your loved one can live.

174
00:10:23,322 --> 00:10:24,390
That is also your responsibility.

175
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:28,527
This is the choice you should make.

176
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:35,001
Let him go.

177
00:11:10,469 --> 00:11:11,003
Director Lin.

178
00:11:11,037 --> 00:11:11,904
Director Lin! Director Lin!

179
00:11:14,373 --> 00:11:14,774
Xiao Lin.

180
00:11:16,075 --> 00:11:16,509
Xiao Lin.

181
00:11:16,742 --> 00:11:17,276
Lin Yi.

182
00:11:18,411 --> 00:11:18,878
Lin Yi.

183
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:20,012
Lin Yi.

184
00:12:08,527 --> 00:12:09,028
Xiaorui.

185
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:17,136
Xiaorui.

186
00:12:22,975 --> 00:12:23,476
Yi.

187
00:12:58,277 --> 00:12:58,744
Yi.

188
00:13:01,413 --> 00:13:01,947
Brother.

189
00:13:17,229 --> 00:13:17,997
I'm sorry.

190
00:13:23,569 --> 00:13:25,304
I couldn't keep my promise.

191
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,142
You've already done so well.

192
00:13:31,677 --> 00:13:32,478
You've worked hard.

193
00:13:35,214 --> 00:13:35,948
Do you remember

194
00:13:36,081 --> 00:13:37,216
the book we read together?

195
00:13:41,086 --> 00:13:42,555
When someone leaves the earth,

196
00:13:43,589 --> 00:13:45,524
a new star appears in the sky.

197
00:13:47,693 --> 00:13:48,494
Why do all of you

198
00:13:48,527 --> 00:13:50,095
have to become stars?

199
00:13:55,201 --> 00:13:56,969
Why do you have to go to the sky?

200
00:14:00,873 --> 00:14:02,808
Why leave me behind?

201
00:14:24,263 --> 00:14:26,365
Why did you have to leave?

202
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,643
To shine a little light

203
00:14:38,244 --> 00:14:39,211
shed a little light

204
00:15:42,074 --> 00:15:43,309
I want to say goodbye to him.

205
00:18:10,489 --> 00:18:10,989
He said a butterfly

206
00:18:10,989 --> 00:18:11,957
could create a whirlwind of love

207
00:18:12,291 --> 00:18:13,792
with every flap of its wings.

208
00:18:14,226 --> 00:18:14,760
But today,

209
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:16,962
he tied my shoelaces

210
00:18:16,962 --> 00:18:17,863
with a surgical knot.

211
00:18:18,063 --> 00:18:19,164
It looked awful.

212
00:18:20,199 --> 00:18:21,467
If he can't even tie a bow,

213
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:23,068
how am I supposed to flap my butterfly wings?

214
00:18:23,368 --> 00:18:25,037
Fine. Next time I'll tie you a bow.

215
00:20:06,838 --> 00:20:07,773
I'll get your clothes.

216
00:21:21,413 --> 00:21:22,280
Why did you dig out

217
00:21:22,314 --> 00:21:23,048
this shirt?

218
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:24,850
Did Yi wash it?

219
00:21:26,918 --> 00:21:27,452
The colors all ran.

220
00:21:27,519 --> 00:21:28,754
I thought you'd never wear it again.

221
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:31,490
I'll let him off this time.

222
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:32,991
Because I think it looks good.

223
00:21:33,592 --> 00:21:34,826
And everyone's colors

224
00:21:35,193 --> 00:21:35,827
are all on it.

225
00:21:36,528 --> 00:21:37,062
That makes it meaningful.

226
00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:38,964
Fine.

227
00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:40,232
It's one of a kind.

228
00:21:41,033 --> 00:21:41,833
No one else will have the same shirt.

229
00:21:43,535 --> 00:21:44,303
I've already decided.

230
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:45,971
On Dad's birthday,

231
00:21:46,271 --> 00:21:47,005
I'll wear this

232
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:48,573
and take the spiriranthes to see him.

233
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:50,676
Okay.

234
00:21:51,176 --> 00:21:52,010
And I'll complain to him

235
00:21:53,278 --> 00:21:55,213
that Yi is still unreliable

236
00:21:55,747 --> 00:21:56,615
and has gained weight again.

237
00:22:35,287 --> 00:22:36,321
Remember to take a nap.

238
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:39,791
I know, you nag.

239
00:22:40,358 --> 00:22:41,360
Bye-bye.

240
00:22:43,595 --> 00:22:45,230
You still can't say goodbye properly.

241
00:23:17,796 --> 00:23:18,563
Are you home?

242
00:23:23,034 --> 00:23:23,969
Did you get everything?

243
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:07,846
Lin Yi.

244
00:25:47,045 --> 00:25:48,213
As the first cold wave

245
00:25:48,413 --> 00:25:49,881
of 2024 sweeps through,

246
00:25:50,315 --> 00:25:51,283
powerful cold air

247
00:25:51,483 --> 00:25:53,385
is pushing the warm, humid air southward.

248
00:25:54,052 --> 00:25:54,953
It's only November,

249
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:56,922
yet Dongjiang has welcomed

250
00:25:56,988 --> 00:25:58,023
its earliest first snow in ten years.

251
00:25:58,890 --> 00:26:00,492
According to the Dongjiang Meteorological Center,

252
00:26:00,692 --> 00:26:01,993
today's high

253
00:26:02,127 --> 00:26:03,194
will be around one degree Celsius.

254
00:26:03,328 --> 00:26:04,162
Winds will be strong,

255
00:26:04,529 --> 00:26:05,530
with northwesterly winds at Force 5

256
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:06,932
and gusts at Force 6 to 7,

257
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:08,733
and even stronger along the coast.

258
00:26:09,868 --> 00:26:11,036
The snow is so heavy.

259
00:26:11,603 --> 00:26:12,203
Let's go.

260
00:26:21,546 --> 00:26:22,714
It's snowing. Look.

261
00:27:06,224 --> 00:27:06,791
You really didn't need

262
00:27:06,825 --> 00:27:07,993
to come all this way.

263
00:27:09,294 --> 00:27:10,328
I thought it would be better

264
00:27:10,362 --> 00:27:11,129
to come in person.

265
00:27:13,565 --> 00:27:14,065
How...

266
00:27:14,599 --> 00:27:15,200
how are you?

267
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:16,201
Are you okay?

268
00:27:19,804 --> 00:27:20,605
If there's anything

269
00:27:20,639 --> 00:27:21,640
I can help with,

270
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:23,208
please tell me.

271
00:27:28,079 --> 00:27:28,947
Director Zhou is here.

272
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:30,215
Sorry I wasn't there to welcome you.

273
00:27:31,783 --> 00:27:32,517
You two talk.

274
00:27:38,556 --> 00:27:39,024
Director Zhou.

275
00:27:39,758 --> 00:27:40,692
Have some fruit first.

276
00:27:41,292 --> 00:27:41,793
Here, have some water.

277
00:27:42,527 --> 00:27:43,528
No need to be so polite, Mr. Qin.

278
00:27:44,129 --> 00:27:45,063
I mainly came today

279
00:27:45,130 --> 00:27:45,964
to thank you in person

280
00:27:46,264 --> 00:27:46,865
for helping arrange

281
00:27:46,865 --> 00:27:48,066
the helicopter.

282
00:27:48,767 --> 00:27:49,267
Director Zhou,

283
00:27:49,401 --> 00:27:50,735
please don't mention it.

284
00:27:51,302 --> 00:27:52,437
I didn't manage to help in the end.

285
00:27:53,605 --> 00:27:54,773
It still makes me feel

286
00:27:55,473 --> 00:27:56,307
pretty awful.

287
00:27:57,242 --> 00:27:58,610
He was so young.

288
00:27:59,911 --> 00:28:00,712
Such a shame.

289
00:28:05,717 --> 00:28:06,951
How much did you spend in total?

290
00:28:07,318 --> 00:28:07,919
I'll transfer it to you.

291
00:28:08,953 --> 00:28:09,654
I didn't spend anything.

292
00:28:09,854 --> 00:28:11,589
The flight never happened.

293
00:28:13,725 --> 00:28:15,093
But arranging the aircraft

294
00:28:15,160 --> 00:28:15,827
and the personnel

295
00:28:15,927 --> 00:28:16,828
must have cost something.

296
00:28:17,629 --> 00:28:18,363
Honestly,

297
00:28:18,530 --> 00:28:19,130
it really wasn't much.

298
00:28:19,831 --> 00:28:21,232
I asked a friend for help.

299
00:28:21,633 --> 00:28:23,001
It was a personal favor.

300
00:28:23,802 --> 00:28:24,936
He didn't charge me.

301
00:28:25,270 --> 00:28:26,371
If I took your money,

302
00:28:26,704 --> 00:28:27,605
what kind of person would that make me?

303
00:28:28,473 --> 00:28:29,040
No, but...

304
00:28:29,307 --> 00:28:29,708
Director Zhou,

305
00:28:30,375 --> 00:28:31,176
there has never been

306
00:28:31,409 --> 00:28:32,744
any financial transaction between us,

307
00:28:32,744 --> 00:28:33,244
right?

308
00:28:33,511 --> 00:28:34,112
If you suddenly

309
00:28:34,112 --> 00:28:35,113
transferred me money,

310
00:28:35,113 --> 00:28:36,548
I'd have a lot of explaining to do

311
00:28:37,082 --> 00:28:38,483
if anyone investigated later.

312
00:28:39,517 --> 00:28:39,918
That's true.

313
00:28:40,151 --> 00:28:41,386
Then I'll settle it directly with them.

314
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:42,687
Director Zhou,

315
00:28:45,723 --> 00:28:46,191
really,

316
00:28:46,891 --> 00:28:48,526
I deeply admire

317
00:28:49,427 --> 00:28:51,062
the kind of person you are.

318
00:28:51,329 --> 00:28:52,163
Even if we weren't

319
00:28:52,197 --> 00:28:53,131
in a client-vendor relationship,

320
00:28:54,199 --> 00:28:55,166
I'd still hope

321
00:28:55,567 --> 00:28:56,468
to have a friend like you.

322
00:28:56,868 --> 00:28:57,368
You did it for your brother.

323
00:28:57,602 --> 00:28:58,570
I did it for my friend.

324
00:29:00,004 --> 00:29:01,406
It's the same principle.

325
00:29:01,639 --> 00:29:02,874
Having the chance

326
00:29:03,041 --> 00:29:04,409
to do even one small thing for you

327
00:29:04,876 --> 00:29:05,543
is an honor for me.

328
00:29:05,610 --> 00:29:06,344
So let's not

329
00:29:08,313 --> 00:29:08,847
stand on ceremony.

330
00:29:09,047 --> 00:29:10,048
Come on.

331
00:29:14,319 --> 00:29:15,353
Have some fruit.

332
00:29:17,689 --> 00:29:19,324
Director Lin, that's enough.

333
00:29:20,091 --> 00:29:20,925
It looks all right.

334
00:29:20,992 --> 00:29:21,493
Has he had

335
00:29:21,493 --> 00:29:22,293
an echocardiogram and 24-hour Holter monitoring?

336
00:29:22,627 --> 00:29:23,094
Yes.

337
00:29:23,228 --> 00:29:23,995
There were no major problems.

338
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:25,864
But genetic testing shows

339
00:29:26,030 --> 00:29:27,132
he carries a pathogenic mutation.

340
00:29:27,532 --> 00:29:28,399
And the probability

341
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:29,267
of developing the disease is unclear.

342
00:29:29,634 --> 00:29:30,401
Actually,

343
00:29:30,435 --> 00:29:31,503
you don't need to worry too much.

344
00:29:31,803 --> 00:29:32,570
For now,

345
00:29:32,670 --> 00:29:34,105
we can rule out dilated cardiomyopathy.

346
00:29:34,873 --> 00:29:35,673
His current insomnia,

347
00:29:35,707 --> 00:29:37,308
chest pain, and palpitations

348
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:38,510
are probably

349
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:40,111
mainly psychological.

350
00:29:43,915 --> 00:29:44,482
But this can't

351
00:29:44,482 --> 00:29:45,450
go on indefinitely.

352
00:29:46,251 --> 00:29:47,385
You're right to take it seriously.

353
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:49,454
This kind of grief-related stress

354
00:29:49,721 --> 00:29:50,889
is harmful even

355
00:29:50,922 --> 00:29:51,823
to an average person.

356
00:29:52,190 --> 00:29:53,224
Let alone someone

357
00:29:53,224 --> 00:29:54,025
in Director Lin's condition.

358
00:29:54,592 --> 00:29:55,693
We really can't be careless.

359
00:29:56,094 --> 00:29:57,162
He needs regular follow-ups.

360
00:30:01,432 --> 00:30:02,066
What's wrong?

361
00:30:04,502 --> 00:30:05,103
Are you okay?

362
00:30:06,204 --> 00:30:07,238
He fell asleep

363
00:30:08,973 --> 00:30:09,874
in such a noisy place.

364
00:30:14,813 --> 00:30:15,346
Maybe

365
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:17,248
he should see a psychologist.

366
00:30:23,054 --> 00:30:23,655
Director Lin.

367
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:25,690
Should I schedule the next follow-up

368
00:30:25,957 --> 00:30:27,158
for six months

369
00:30:27,492 --> 00:30:28,092
Six months.

370
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:29,127
Six months, just to be safe.

371
00:30:30,328 --> 00:30:30,728
Okay.

372
00:30:36,201 --> 00:30:37,035
Thank you, Director Wang.

373
00:30:39,470 --> 00:30:40,405
You don't need to be too nervous.

374
00:30:40,805 --> 00:30:41,706
Let's get him admitted first.

375
00:30:42,006 --> 00:30:42,707
Thank you.

376
00:30:43,107 --> 00:30:43,808
Come with me.

377
00:30:43,875 --> 00:30:44,809
I'll help you with the admission.

378
00:30:51,282 --> 00:30:51,883
Are you okay?

379
00:30:56,921 --> 00:30:57,956
You didn't sleep again last night, did you?

380
00:31:01,125 --> 00:31:01,626
I couldn't.

381
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:05,463
Why don't you take annual leave

382
00:31:06,164 --> 00:31:07,031
and get some proper rest?

383
00:31:08,032 --> 00:31:08,633
If I stay home,

384
00:31:08,666 --> 00:31:09,667
I won't know what to do.

385
00:31:12,804 --> 00:31:13,304
Maybe

386
00:31:14,639 --> 00:31:16,007
we should finish this week's appointments

387
00:31:17,008 --> 00:31:18,509
and suspend the joint clinic for a while.

388
00:31:20,011 --> 00:31:20,812
Zhang Zhen and Liu Dong

389
00:31:20,812 --> 00:31:22,146
have opened their own clinics anyway.

390
00:31:30,989 --> 00:31:32,323
The slots for the European summit

391
00:31:32,323 --> 00:31:33,391
have all been finalized.

392
00:31:33,825 --> 00:31:34,826
They're already

393
00:31:34,826 --> 00:31:35,994
starting the visa applications.

394
00:31:36,828 --> 00:31:37,996
Dr. Zhang told me

395
00:31:38,429 --> 00:31:39,964
he never expected to get a slot.

396
00:31:40,064 --> 00:31:40,965
He's thrilled.

397
00:31:43,368 --> 00:31:44,736
He usually has it hard.

398
00:31:45,803 --> 00:31:47,438
He works tirelessly and conscientiously.

399
00:31:48,673 --> 00:31:49,774
This is a good chance

400
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:51,476
for him to recharge and relax.

401
00:31:51,609 --> 00:31:52,076
That's good.

402
00:31:52,477 --> 00:31:53,544
And this summit

403
00:31:53,544 --> 00:31:54,512
is highly valuable.

404
00:31:55,246 --> 00:31:55,947
It's a great opportunity

405
00:31:56,047 --> 00:31:57,248
for him to learn and gain experience.

406
00:31:57,415 --> 00:31:58,283
It'll help him.

407
00:32:00,752 --> 00:32:01,452
With a director

408
00:32:01,486 --> 00:32:02,787
as considerate as you,

409
00:32:03,521 --> 00:32:04,555
he'd probably work himself to the bone

410
00:32:04,656 --> 00:32:05,790
without complaint.

411
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:09,994
Cardiac Surgery

412
00:32:10,561 --> 00:32:11,996
is definitely sending Director Sheng himself, right?

413
00:32:13,731 --> 00:32:14,165
Yes.

414
00:32:15,566 --> 00:32:17,201
See? Both are department directors,

415
00:32:17,669 --> 00:32:18,403
but at critical moments,

416
00:32:18,903 --> 00:32:20,038
you can tell who's better.

417
00:32:26,811 --> 00:32:27,845
How is

418
00:32:29,714 --> 00:32:30,615
Director Lin?

419
00:32:34,652 --> 00:32:35,320
Not very well.

420
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:42,093
Maybe he doesn't want us to worry.

421
00:32:43,394 --> 00:32:44,762
He refuses to tell us anything.

422
00:32:45,930 --> 00:32:47,031
He keeps everything bottled up.

423
00:32:51,569 --> 00:32:52,870
Honestly, it might be better

424
00:32:53,171 --> 00:32:54,305
if he cried or made a scene,

425
00:32:54,439 --> 00:32:55,206
and let it out.

426
00:32:55,873 --> 00:32:56,841
If he keeps it all inside,

427
00:32:57,275 --> 00:32:58,943
even if he looks calm,

428
00:32:59,243 --> 00:33:00,144
his heart

429
00:33:00,144 --> 00:33:01,346
may already be shattered.

430
00:33:02,046 --> 00:33:03,214
He'll make himself sick.

431
00:33:06,484 --> 00:33:07,785
I urged him to take some time off,

432
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:09,487
but he wouldn't listen.

433
00:33:12,357 --> 00:33:13,157
How about

434
00:33:14,392 --> 00:33:15,760
I apply for

435
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:16,761
a summit slot for him?

436
00:33:17,128 --> 00:33:18,830
It could give him a change of scenery.

437
00:33:21,432 --> 00:33:22,400
That's a good idea.

438
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:23,468
It is.

439
00:33:24,569 --> 00:33:25,470
Right now, only

440
00:33:25,470 --> 00:33:26,571
professional matters

441
00:33:26,604 --> 00:33:28,006
can get him energized.

442
00:33:28,606 --> 00:33:29,273
But I'm not sure

443
00:33:29,273 --> 00:33:29,974
he'd be willing to go.

444
00:33:30,408 --> 00:33:31,542
I'll talk to him first.

445
00:33:31,876 --> 00:33:33,644
If that doesn't work, I'll ask Director Sheng.

446
00:33:34,278 --> 00:33:35,513
He'll listen to Director Sheng.

447
00:33:36,414 --> 00:33:37,482
As long as he's willing,

448
00:33:37,615 --> 00:33:38,916
I'll do whatever it takes

449
00:33:38,916 --> 00:33:39,851
to secure that slot.

450
00:33:44,489 --> 00:33:45,156
You get back to work.

451
00:33:45,523 --> 00:33:46,691
I'll ask about the slot.

452
00:33:49,927 --> 00:33:50,395
By the way,

453
00:33:51,929 --> 00:33:52,530
is Senlin due

454
00:33:52,530 --> 00:33:53,364
for his checkup this month?

455
00:33:55,266 --> 00:33:56,167
If it's convenient,

456
00:33:56,401 --> 00:33:56,968
I'd like to arrange

457
00:33:56,968 --> 00:33:57,869
an MRI for him

458
00:33:58,169 --> 00:33:59,037
and review it personally.

459
00:34:02,173 --> 00:34:02,774
That's very thoughtful.

460
00:34:03,241 --> 00:34:03,674
Thank you.

461
00:34:05,243 --> 00:34:06,277
No need to be so polite.

462
00:34:10,748 --> 00:34:11,182
I'm leaving.

463
00:34:15,853 --> 00:34:16,721
As you know,

464
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:17,488
the European summit slots

465
00:34:17,522 --> 00:34:18,990
are extremely competitive this year.

466
00:34:19,323 --> 00:34:20,158
I truly had to pull

467
00:34:20,158 --> 00:34:21,125
every string I could

468
00:34:21,192 --> 00:34:22,393
to get one more.

469
00:34:23,161 --> 00:34:23,895
After all,

470
00:34:24,128 --> 00:34:25,930
Director Lin is in a special situation.

471
00:34:26,764 --> 00:34:27,999
For such an important summit,

472
00:34:28,232 --> 00:34:29,133
Cardiology

473
00:34:29,267 --> 00:34:30,435
is only sending Zhang Zhen.

474
00:34:31,102 --> 00:34:31,869
Had I known,

475
00:34:31,969 --> 00:34:33,237
we might as well have given this slot

476
00:34:33,237 --> 00:34:34,372
to Lin Yi directly.

477
00:34:36,441 --> 00:34:37,108
Had we known...

478
00:34:37,308 --> 00:34:38,376
No one could have predicted

479
00:34:38,376 --> 00:34:39,844
this would happen.

480
00:34:41,746 --> 00:34:42,447
All right.

481
00:34:42,680 --> 00:34:43,915
It may be good for him to get away.

482
00:34:44,515 --> 00:34:45,049
I'll talk to him.

483
00:34:45,950 --> 00:34:47,185
Thank you, Director Sheng.

484
00:34:49,120 --> 00:34:50,888
Manager Ouyang, you really think of everything.

485
00:34:51,556 --> 00:34:52,623
What I'm thinking is,

486
00:34:52,957 --> 00:34:54,926
if we can help Director Lin

487
00:34:54,992 --> 00:34:55,927
move forward sooner,

488
00:34:56,194 --> 00:34:57,595
that also helps ease

489
00:34:57,595 --> 00:34:58,429
your burden, doesn't it?

490
00:34:59,030 --> 00:35:00,465
Not only mine, I imagine.

491
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:10,007
I'll get you another hoodie.

492
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,281
These regular medicines

493
00:35:17,281 --> 00:35:18,115
will go in

494
00:35:18,149 --> 00:35:19,317
this little white pouch.

495
00:35:19,784 --> 00:35:21,085
Be careful.

496
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:21,886
Don't catch a chill.

497
00:35:28,993 --> 00:35:29,894
And your toiletries—

498
00:35:29,894 --> 00:35:31,195
I've packed them separately

499
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:32,563
so they're easy to take.

500
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:37,268
Xiaoran.

501
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:47,078
I want to sell the old house.

502
00:35:52,350 --> 00:35:52,884
Okay.

503
00:35:56,754 --> 00:35:57,688
Think about whether

504
00:35:57,688 --> 00:35:58,322
there's anything there

505
00:35:58,322 --> 00:35:59,524
you want to keep.

506
00:36:00,224 --> 00:36:01,025
Tell me.

507
00:36:02,393 --> 00:36:03,794
I'll go sort through it

508
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:04,362
and bring it over.

509
00:36:07,798 --> 00:36:08,432
No need.

510
00:36:11,802 --> 00:36:12,570
When I come back,

511
00:36:13,704 --> 00:36:14,639
I don't want to live here either.

512
00:36:19,477 --> 00:36:20,344
Let's move.

513
00:36:22,914 --> 00:36:23,481
Okay.

514
00:36:25,149 --> 00:36:26,384
We'll look for a new place.

515
00:36:43,534 --> 00:36:44,135
This time,

516
00:36:45,636 --> 00:36:46,204
we'll find a home

517
00:36:46,204 --> 00:36:47,071
you like.

518
00:36:52,276 --> 00:36:52,710
I'm leaving.

519
00:36:55,079 --> 00:36:55,646
Wait.

520
00:36:58,015 --> 00:36:59,183
Not one I like.

521
00:36:59,850 --> 00:37:01,118
One we like.

522
00:37:15,132 --> 00:37:15,766
This

523
00:37:18,769 --> 00:37:20,071
was given to us by Xiaorui.

524
00:38:10,121 --> 00:38:11,289
I told him his craftsmanship was bad.

525
00:38:14,191 --> 00:38:14,825
Lin Yi.

526
00:38:16,494 --> 00:38:17,528
Let's get married.

527
00:38:22,667 --> 00:38:24,268
I want a wedding by the sea.

528
00:38:24,702 --> 00:38:25,569
We don't have to wait until spring.

529
00:38:26,404 --> 00:38:27,638
The sea is beautiful in winter too.

530
00:38:30,574 --> 00:38:31,842
Let me be your family.

531
00:38:50,628 --> 00:38:51,962
Xiaorui and I designed countless

532
00:38:51,996 --> 00:38:53,130
ways to propose.

533
00:38:58,569 --> 00:38:59,770
I just never thought it would happen like this.

534
00:39:06,010 --> 00:39:06,544
I do.

535
00:39:12,316 --> 00:39:13,517
Give me some time to recover.

536
00:39:28,365 --> 00:39:28,833
I'm leaving.

537
00:40:36,801 --> 00:40:37,368
Ouyang.

538
00:40:37,601 --> 00:40:38,102
Mr. Qin.

539
00:40:38,369 --> 00:40:39,904
There are five revisions.

540
00:40:40,070 --> 00:40:40,971
I've compiled them

541
00:40:41,038 --> 00:40:41,639
into an editable document

542
00:40:41,639 --> 00:40:42,573
and sent it to your WeChat

543
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:43,374
and email.

544
00:40:44,108 --> 00:40:45,042
Okay, okay.

545
00:40:46,644 --> 00:40:47,111
Mr. Qin.

546
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:49,079
Did everything go smoothly there today?

547
00:40:49,847 --> 00:40:50,414
Today?

548
00:40:52,483 --> 00:40:53,384
The meeting

549
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:54,185
is over.

550
00:40:54,785 --> 00:40:55,386
I just

551
00:40:55,452 --> 00:40:56,720
talked with Sheng Nian for a while.

552
00:40:57,922 --> 00:40:59,523
He's still somewhat unhappy

553
00:40:59,523 --> 00:41:01,125
that you helped Zhou Xiaofeng

554
00:41:01,158 --> 00:41:02,159
with the fourth-generation vascular plug.

555
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:04,028
But fortunately, I calmed him down.

556
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:07,331
Don't worry.

557
00:41:07,932 --> 00:41:08,465
I know.

558
00:41:08,566 --> 00:41:10,134
I'll keep things balanced.

559
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:12,002
Ouyang.

560
00:41:12,169 --> 00:41:13,070
I get the feeling

561
00:41:13,771 --> 00:41:16,006
Sheng Nian is determined

562
00:41:16,173 --> 00:41:17,074
to move into transcatheter valve procedures.

563
00:41:17,408 --> 00:41:18,976
He mentioned it at the forum today too.

564
00:41:19,910 --> 00:41:20,611
It looks like

565
00:41:20,744 --> 00:41:22,480
a war between Cardiology and Cardiac Surgery at Dongli

566
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:23,814
is about to break out.

567
00:41:25,583 --> 00:41:26,317
Isn't that exactly

568
00:41:26,317 --> 00:41:27,518
what you wanted to see?

569
00:41:27,985 --> 00:41:28,953
When the snipe and clam fight,

570
00:41:29,119 --> 00:41:29,887
the fisherman profits.

571
00:41:32,189 --> 00:41:32,790
All right, all right.

572
00:41:33,524 --> 00:41:35,226
The fisherman is going to dinner with them now.

573
00:41:35,426 --> 00:41:35,993
I'm hanging up.

574
00:41:36,560 --> 00:41:37,394
Okay, bye.

575
00:41:37,761 --> 00:41:38,395
Bye.

576
00:41:46,237 --> 00:41:47,805
I truly learned a lot

577
00:41:47,972 --> 00:41:49,173
from your talk at the forum today.

578
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,107
It was extremely enlightening.

579
00:41:50,508 --> 00:41:51,208
Mr. Qin, thank you for your hard work.

580
00:41:51,442 --> 00:41:52,443
It's what I should do.

581
00:41:52,710 --> 00:41:53,711
I must toast you with this glass.

582
00:41:54,111 --> 00:41:55,145
Take it easy. I'll finish mine.

583
00:41:56,213 --> 00:41:56,714
Thank you, Director.

584
00:41:56,914 --> 00:41:57,615
If it doesn't work well,

585
00:41:57,681 --> 00:41:58,883
we'll never force it.

586
00:41:59,884 --> 00:42:00,584
Take your time using it.

587
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:03,554
Here.

588
00:42:05,489 --> 00:42:06,123
Director Lin.

589
00:42:06,991 --> 00:42:07,625
Let me pour you some wine.

590
00:42:08,158 --> 00:42:08,759
I don't drink.

591
00:42:09,093 --> 00:42:09,693
Just one glass.

592
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:10,294
I can't.

593
00:42:10,694 --> 00:42:11,161
Mr. Qin.

594
00:42:12,029 --> 00:42:12,630
I'll drink with you.

595
00:42:13,063 --> 00:42:14,331
All right, all right. No pressuring anyone.

596
00:42:14,331 --> 00:42:14,832
Drink as you like.

597
00:42:15,266 --> 00:42:15,666
Sorry.

598
00:42:15,666 --> 00:42:16,233
No, no, no.

599
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:18,269
What is it? Still jet-lagged?

600
00:42:19,970 --> 00:42:20,437
A little.

601
00:42:21,071 --> 00:42:21,672
Then drink less.

602
00:42:21,839 --> 00:42:23,173
One glass is fine. It'll help you sleep.

603
00:42:24,808 --> 00:42:26,610
Director, I barely drink.

604
00:42:28,879 --> 00:42:30,481
Everyone knows alcohol isn't good.

605
00:42:31,115 --> 00:42:32,283
But it can make people happy.

606
00:42:33,250 --> 00:42:35,452
In clinical practice, I've met

607
00:42:35,753 --> 00:42:36,654
people with congenital conditions

608
00:42:37,521 --> 00:42:38,856
who had no idea what they had

609
00:42:39,356 --> 00:42:40,324
and lived without restrictions,

610
00:42:40,424 --> 00:42:41,592
yet still reached their seventies or eighties.

611
00:42:41,926 --> 00:42:42,760
As long as there's moderation,

612
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:44,395
don't make life too hard on yourself.

613
00:42:53,037 --> 00:42:53,504
That's true.

614
00:42:54,171 --> 00:42:55,639
No amount of caution can keep every storm away.

615
00:42:55,773 --> 00:42:56,674
A little drink won't hurt.
